hopobject.body: What do you like doing in your spare time? hunterglam.com This 15-acre corn maze is the biggest in Wisconsin and embraces the old-school sea monster, the Kraken, for its theme this year. Along the way, youâre challenged (with the promise of prizes) to find seven mailboxes and eight secret locations. The farm also has hay rides, farm animals, and a one-night spookfest on Oct. 26 called Zompocalpyse. Open weekends only through Sept. 22 and then Fri.-Sun., Sept. 28-Oct. 27. Admission: $8.50 for ages 12 and up; $6.50 for ages 6-11; free for ages 5 and under.
